# Build context for the matcher image is cloud-webapp/matcher/ (deploy-matcher.sh
# runs `gcloud builds submit $REPO_ROOT/matcher`), so the cloud-webapp/.dockerignore
# does NOT apply here — Docker uses the .dockerignore at the context root. The
# matcher Dockerfile copies `*.py` by glob (so new modules are never silently
# omitted); these excludes keep tests, caches, and local-only data out of the image.
**/test_*.py
**/conftest.py
**/requirements-test.txt
**/__pycache__
**/.pytest_cache
**/pytest-cache-files-*
**/.venv
local_store/
eval/
*.log
.DS_Store
